/*
 * Malloc Library: 
 * A library that provide memory allocation and deallocation functionality on program. 
 * Allowing program to be reserve memory space from the system's heap at runtime. 
 * 
 * Usage:
 * @param size - number of bytes to allocate
 *
 * @return a pointer to the first byte of the allocated memory block.
 *
 * void * malloc(size_t size);
 * 
 * @param p - pointer returned to the user by a call to malloc
 * 
 * void free(void * p);
 * 
 */


